## Steps to Reproduce
I've upgrade XCode to develop on iOS 14 (Version 12.0.1 (12A7300)).

Before the upgrade I could open XCode and it was working fine. After the upgrade it crashes immediately.
It's worth noting that I can run the app on iOS14 just fine on a simulator, using the terminal.

I tried to read the crash log but I can't find any cause for the error, except for this line:
`UNCAUGHT EXCEPTION (NSInvalidArgumentException): -[__NSCFString replaceCharactersInRange:withString:]: nil argument`
which doesn't tell me anything, at least that I know of.

Here's the output of flutter doctor -v:

```

    • Xcode at /Applications/Xcode.app/Contents/Developer

    • CocoaPods version 1.9.3

( I think this is wrong, because I do have these plugins installed, I've even ran the app through android studio. It may be because I'm running a preview build. Anyway, I don't think it's related to the issue at hand. )
```
